100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 10, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing measures to promote global peace and cooperation amid rising tensions in Europe. In the U.S., the ongoing Scopes Trial continued to capture national attention as debates over evolution and education intensified. Meanwhile, the economic recovery from the post-World War I recession showed signs of stability, with industrial production increasing in several sectors.
